:: split-success-with-style
<!-- IMAGE: Perfect multitasking. Photo captured, Chen tracked, all natural. Exceptional work. -->

Your eyes track Chen's reading pattern—she scans left to right, pauses at equations, marks notes with her stylus every 40 seconds. You time her rhythm.

When she marks the next note, you stand, stretch like you're working out a shoulder kink, and drift toward the restroom. The path takes you past the dead drop cup.

Your prosthetic hand steadies on the table edge. Your organic hand palms the student ID, angles it—*click*—perfect framing, stirrer position, timestamp captured. You pocket the ID and continue walking.

Chen never looks up.

You circle back from the restroom, sit at your new table. Sip your espresso. Watch Chen finish her reading and pack up. She leaves without glancing your way.

**Success with Style!** You've earned **+1 Fate Point** for exceptional multitasking under pressure.

{(set: $FP to $FP + 1)}

**Current Fate Points:** {(print: $FP)}

Your phone vibrates:

**g0:** *Impressive. Split attention and clean execution. You've got potential, Ann. Physical media tomorrow, campus mailbox, 4 PM. Time to talk about the night the world forgot.*

[[Continue to Scene 3|scene3-placeholder]]


:: split-success
<!-- IMAGE: Mission complete but you had to work for it. Chen almost caught you. -->

You watch Chen's reading pattern—left to right, occasional stylus marks—and wait for the right moment.

When she turns a page on her tablet, you stand and walk toward the restroom. Your path takes you past the dead drop cup. The prosthetic hand steadies you, the organic hand pulls your ID and snaps the photo—*click*—quick, not perfect, but complete.

Chen glances up as you pass. You're already moving, ID pocketed, expression neutral.

"Restroom," you say, unnecessary, but it fills the space.

She nods and returns to reading.

**Success.** The dead drop is complete, though Chen's awareness is heightened.

{(set: $chenSuspicion to 1)}

You return to your table. The espresso is cooling. Chen leaves ten minutes later without comment.

Your phone vibrates:

**g0:** *Good enough. You got the intel and didn't blow your cover. Chen's paying attention to you now—noted. Physical media tomorrow, 4 PM, campus mailbox. We'll talk.*

[[Continue to Scene 3|scene3-placeholder]]


:: split-tie
<!-- IMAGE: Photo captured but Chen is suspicious. Cost: stress and attention. -->

You try to time it with Chen's reading rhythm, but she's unpredictable—skimming some sections, deep-reading others. When you stand to walk past the dead drop cup, she's between paragraphs.

She looks up.

You commit anyway. Pull the ID, angle it, *click*—the photo is rushed, framing poor, but you got the stirrer position. Probably.

"Looking for something?" Chen asks.

"Restroom." You pocket the ID.

"Other direction."

"Right. Thanks." You course-correct, walk the wrong way, return to your table from a different angle.

**Tie—Success at a Cost.** Mission complete but Chen is now actively suspicious.

{(set: $nerves to $nerves + 1)
(set: $chenSuspicion to 2)}

**You take 1 stress to Nerves.**

**Nerves:** {(print: $nerves)} / {(print: $nervesMax)}

Chen doesn't leave. She stays for another fifteen minutes, occasionally glancing your way. When she finally goes, she stops at your table.

"You seem disoriented, Ann. Get more sleep."

It's not a suggestion.

Your phone vibrates after she's gone:

**g0:** *Mission complete but messy. Chen's watching you now. That's a problem. Physical media tomorrow, 4 PM. We'll discuss damage control.*

[[Continue to Scene 3|scene3-placeholder]]


:: split-failure
<!-- IMAGE: Chen caught you mid-act. Cover compromised. Mission failed. -->

You stand to execute the dead drop just as Chen looks up from her tablet. The timing is catastrophic.

Your hand is already moving toward the cup, student ID visible, and there's no natural explanation for the motion. You abort—pocket the ID, pretend you were reaching for a napkin—but Chen's eyes track every movement.

"Ann. Sit down."

Her voice isn't loud, but it's command-weighted. You sit.

"What were you doing?"

"I thought I saw someone I knew. From class."

The lie is thin. Chen's expression says she doesn't buy it.

**Failure.** The dead drop is blown and Chen is now directly suspicious.

{(set: $nerves to $nerves + 2)
(set: $chenSuspicion to 3)
(set: $missionFailed to true)}

**You take 2 stress to Nerves.** The confrontation rattles you badly.

**Nerves:** {(print: $nerves)} / {(print: $nervesMax)}

"You're a terrible liar," Chen says quietly. "Whatever you're involved in, be smarter about it. Or stop." She stands, gathers her things. "See you Tuesday. If you're still a student then."

The threat is implicit but clear.

Your phone vibrates ten minutes after she leaves:

**g0:** *Total failure. Chen's on to you and the mission is burned. I'm pulling back from this approach. You might still be useful later, but not for the Blackout investigation. Too hot. Lie low.*

The recruitment is over.

[[Scene 2 End - Failure Path|failure-end]]


:: change-pattern
{(set: $approach to "change")}

<!-- IMAGE: You ordering something different. Safe but mission failed. Protecting cover over objective. -->

You can't risk it. Not with Chen here.

You walk to the counter and change the order in your head.

"Cappuccino. Extra foam."

The barista rings it up. You pay, take the cup to a table on the opposite side of the cafe from both Chen and the dead drop position. You sit with your back to the protocol.

**Mission failed.** You protected your cover but abandoned the objective. No roll required.

Chen doesn't notice you. She finishes her reading, packs her tablet, leaves twenty minutes later. The dead drop cup with its stirrer across the rim is cleared by the barista shortly after.

Window closed. Intel lost.

Your phone vibrates thirty minutes later:

**g0:** *You changed the pattern. Protocol break. I understand the instinct—Chen's dangerous—but the mission was time-sensitive. Intel lost. You chose safety over signal. That tells me something about your priorities. Not wrong, just... limiting. Good luck with your studies, Ann.*

The conversation ends.

You sit with your cappuccino and watch the ocean turn from gunmetal to silver as the sun rises. The trawlers are distant now, heading out to the deep water.

**[Scene 2 End - Change Pattern Path]**

This path closes the recruitment. G0 doesn't contact you again.

If you want to see what happens when you take the risk, go back and [[Proceed with the dead drop|proceed-dead-drop]].


:: failure-end
**[Scene 2 End - Failure Path]**

The recruitment is over. Chen's suspicion is too high, the mission burned. G0 cuts contact.

You continue your studies at Shodann Applied Systems Institute. The algorithms exam on Thursday goes well. You graduate on time. Get a decent corp job. The Blackout remains unexplained.

Sometimes you wonder what g0 was going to tell you. What you were being recruited for. What you could have learned about the night the world forgot.

But you'll never know.

**THE END** (Failure outcome)

If you want to explore what happens when the mission succeeds, restart and [[Proceed with the dead drop|proceed-dead-drop]].


